    Click on start button
    Look for Command Prompt
    Right click on the top finding result
    Pick Run as administrator
    Write the command “bcdedit” and press enter
    Note the reoveryenabled and identifier values under the Windows Startup Loader region. The values should be the same as:

identifier: {current}

recoveryenabled: yes

    The command that users will type in order to deactivate self-initiated fixing in Windows 10 is:

bcdedit /set {current} recoveryenabled no

Upon typing the above command, click on Enter.
